---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const webpageSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'WebPage',
  '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#webpage',
  url: 'https://chandrakanojia.com',
  name: 'Enterprise AI Under Operational Control | Chandra Kanojia',
  description: 'Chandra Kanojia helps large regulated enterprises move AI, CRM/Salesforce, workflow, analytics, and platform investment from ambition to governed operating outcomes.',
  isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#website' },
  about: { '@id': 'https://chandrakanojia.com/#person' }
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://chandrakanojia.com' }
  ]
};
---
<PageLayout
  title="Enterprise AI Under Operational Control | Chandra Kanojia"
  description="Chandra Kanojia helps large regulated enterprises move AI, CRM/Salesforce, workflow, analytics, and platform investment from ambition to governed operating outcomes."
  jsonLd={[webpageSchema, breadcrumbSchema]}
>
  <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
    <div class="container hero-grid">
      <div class="hero-main">
        <span class="identity-mark hero-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span></span></span>
        <p class="kicker">Enterprise AI · CRM/Salesforce · Workflow · Regulated Transformation</p>
        <h1 id="hero-title">Enterprise AI, under operational control.</h1>
        <p class="lead hero-copy">
          Chandra Kanojia helps large regulated enterprises move AI, CRM/Salesforce, workflow, analytics, and platform investment from ambition to governed operating outcomes.
        </p>
        <p class="credibility-line">
          Fortune 100 buyer-side execution. Global consulting pattern recognition. Regulated financial-services depth.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href="/executive-profile">View Executive Profile</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href="/enterprise-ai-transformation">Read Enterprise AI Point of View</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="mandate-panel" aria-label="Mandate focus">
        <p class="panel-label">Mandate focus</p>
        <h2>Move from AI ambition to governed execution.</h2>
        <p>
          The durable work is not more demos. It is redesigning work so humans, systems, controls, and AI-enabled execution operate from the same context.
        </p>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section compact" aria-labelledby="authority-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="authority-band">
        <p class="band-label" id="authority-title">Operating context</p>
        <p>
          Fortune 100 regulated environments · Salesforce/CRM modernization · enterprise workflow transformation · service and advisor platforms · analytics and governance · platform reliability · global consulting mandates · insurance, retirement, brokerage, healthcare, and claims transformation
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="mandates-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading compact-heading">
        <p class="kicker">Executive mandates</p>
        <h2 id="mandates-title">Where the work changes the outcome.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mandate-grid">
        <article class="mandate-card">
          <span>01</span>
          <h3>Move AI from pilots to governed execution</h3>
          <p>Design the workflow, controls, adoption path, and operating cadence required for AI to become useful inside regulated work.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="mandate-card">
          <span>02</span>
          <h3>Modernize the systems where work actually moves</h3>
          <p>CRM, case management, analytics, advisor platforms, service operations, and workflow systems become the execution layer for enterprise AI.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="mandate-card">
          <span>03</span>
          <h3>Create operating leverage without losing control</h3>
          <p>Reduce friction, increase capacity, improve experience, and strengthen risk discipline inside complex regulated environments.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt" aria-labelledby="insights-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-heading">
        <div class="intro">
          <p class="kicker">Selected point of view</p>
          <h2 id="insights-title">Current enough for this moment. Durable enough for the next mandate.</h2>
        </div>
        <a class="text-link" href="/insights">View insights</a>
      </div>
      <div class="insight-grid">
        <article class="insight-card">
          <p class="tag">Enterprise AI</p>
          <h3><a href="/insights/ai-moved-from-assistance-to-execution-operating-model-has-not">AI Has Moved From Assistance to Execution. The Operating Model Has Not.</a></h3>
          <p>A board-level operating note on controlled autonomy, evidence discipline, and workflow ownership.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="insight-card">
          <p class="tag">CRM</p>
          <h3><a href="/insights/crm-trap-systems-of-record-never-become-systems-of-action">The CRM Trap: When Systems of Record Never Become Systems of Action.</a></h3>
          <p>Why CRM only creates value when it changes how work moves, decisions get made, and outcomes are governed.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" aria-labelledby="cta-title">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-box mandate-cta">
        <div>
          <p class="panel-label">Discuss the mandate</p>
          <h2 id="cta-title">The right conversation is not whether AI can produce capability. It is whether the enterprise can absorb it.</h2>
          <p>Useful mandates to discuss include governed AI execution, CRM and workflow modernization, operating leverage in regulated environments, and executive confidence in adoption, reliability, governance, and measurable outcomes.</p>
        </div>
        <a class="button" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/chandra-kanojia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
